cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes the use of machine learning (ML) for riverine flood forecasting, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of learned models, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The computational difficulty of building accurate models suggests a focus on computational engineering (cs.CE). The need to leverage local signals for improved global performance suggests a focus on data science (cs.DS). Finally, the proposal to develop ML systems for flood prediction suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
